description:
&lt;p&gt;We have an exciting opportunity for a national Project Manager to join the national informatics programme . Working as part of the Service Transformation team, the post holder will be responsible for delivering specified informatics projects that support the Supporting Professionals element of the current Digital Health and Social care Strategy - Informed Health and Care. Projects are likely to include the implementation into the NHS Wales national architecture of the Digitisation of Eye Care services and the new 111 system and service. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The successful candidate will require project management experience and be expected to apply their knowledge of the NHS as well as project management methodology, tools and techniques to deliver these projects.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing Date: 25/11/2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: David Sheard&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Assistant Director of Service Transformation&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: david.sheard@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
